<section class="col col-720">
  <p>This page is for people who have a degree or are studying towards one, and want to do postgraduate teacher training in England.  To help fund your training, you may be eligible for a bursary or scholarship.</p>
  <h2>What's a bursary?</h2>
  <p>Bursaries are tax-free payments aimed at encouraging graduates to train to teach certain subjects. If you're eligible for a bursary, you'll get it automatically.</p>
  <h2>What's a scholarship?</h2>
  <p>Scholarships are tax-free payments provided by charitable organisations. As well as money, you'll have the opportunity to access benefits like mentoring and networking. If you're eligible, you must apply and only a limited number of scholarships are awarded.</p>
  <h2>What to consider</h2>
  <p>If you're considering a bursary or scholarship, you should know:<ul><li>you cannot receive both</li><li>they're not available for salaried teacher training</li><li>only certain subjects have bursaries and scholarships but this changes every year</li><li>the figures on this page apply if you're starting your training between September 2024 and July 2025</li></p>

